comments.body:
Should we also consider introducing `currentDateTime`, as a high-level alternative to `currentTime`?

Something like:
```scala
    /** Get the current time, represented in the current timezone. */
    val currentDateTime: ZIO[Clock, Nothing, OffsetDateTime] = {
      for {
        millis <- currentTime(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)
        zone   <- timezone
      } yield OffsetDateTime.ofInstant(Instant.ofEpochMilli(millis), zone)
    }
```

I feel this is what the vast majority of people will be using `timezone` for, so it would be convenient to have it built-in.
